      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WHATS GLENDA GOT (9) came from this barrier and dug deep to score at the most recent appearance at Echuca, getting home by 1.8 metres. That made it two wins on the trot she is hard to knock. With even luck she could land the hat trick. BETATHANABOUGHTONE (2) makes her first appearance since February but was tackling stronger races last time in and was readied with a trial. Won over this distance the only time she raced here and she draws well. ARCHAA (1) led in scoring back-to-back wins at this circuit and distance before going under by just a neck as runner-up last time. Has the speed to be prominent form the ace draw. JET TO HEAVEN (8) didn't feature fresh but will be fitter. Had consistent form last time in and won the only time he attempted this distance.",
